Multimedia in HTML
- Multimedia refers to audio, video and animations.
- HTML multimedia includes elements like
    a) <marquee>
    b) <video>
    c) <audio>

Marquee:
- It sets scrolling and sliding content in page.
- You can controll using following attributes:

1. scrollamount    : It sets marquee scrolling speed from 1 to 100.
2. direction    : It sets scrolling direction left, right, up and down.
3. loop        : It defines the number of times to display.

          <marquee scrollamount="20" direction="right" loop="3">
               .... your content........
         </marquee>

4. width & height    : Sets width and height for marquee area.
5. bgcolor        : Sets background color.
6. behavior    : It sets "alternate" behavior, which changes from scroll to slide.

        <marquee behavior="alternate">   Text </marquee>

Video & Audio
- HTML supports videos of following types
    .mkv
    .avi
    .mov
    .mp4
    .ogg etc..
- The <video> element is used to embed videos into page.

Syntax:
    <video src=""  controls   width=""  height="" autoplay poster=""> </video>

- HTML supports audio of type
    .mp3, .wav, .midi etc..

- The <audio> element is used to embed audio files.

    <audio src=""  controls  poster=""> </audio>

Ex:
 <video controls poster="../public/images/java.png" src="../public/videos/js-class.mp4" width="400" height="300"></video>
